  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Balloon-occluded retrograde transvenous obliteration (BRTO) has been effective method to
      manage gastric varices. However, more than one third of patients after BRTO treatment
      experienced worsening of esophageal varices. The present study was designed to evaluate the
      effect of post-BRTO propranolol adminstration on the change of esophageal varices.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
